title: Method Statement for Installation of  Cable Tray & Trunking
description:
Method Statement for Installation of  Cable Tray & Trunking is MEP related documentation suitable for building construction electrical engineering works. The content of the document is well defined according to standard method of installation and it is editable and ready to use.

Cable trays are used as an alternative to open wiring or electrical conduit systems, and are commonly used for cable management in commercial and industrial construction. They are especially useful in situations where changes to a wiring system are anticipated, since new cables can be installed by laying them in the tray, instead of pulling them through a pipe.

File Type: MS word 2007 or above
File Size: 280 KB
